1
00:04:19,077 --> 00:04:22,164
Who's that stumbling around in the dark?

2
00:04:22,330 --> 00:04:26,168
State your business or prepare to get winged.

3
00:04:26,334 --> 00:04:31,089
Calm yourselves, gentlemen. I mean you no harm.

4
00:04:31,715 --> 00:04:34,301
I'm simply a fellow weary traveller.

5
00:04:34,468 --> 00:04:36,511
Whoa, boy.

6
00:04:37,846 --> 00:04:41,641
Good cold evening, gentlemen. I'm looking for a pair of slave traders...

7
00:04:41,808 --> 00:04:44,144
...that go by the name of the Speck Brothers.

8
00:04:44,311 --> 00:04:45,645
Might that be you?

9
00:04:47,147 --> 00:04:49,983
- Who wants to know? - Well, I do.

10
00:04:50,150 --> 00:04:52,862
I'm Dr. King Schultz. This is my horse, Fritz.

11
00:04:53,738 --> 00:04:56,824
- What kind of doctor? - Dentist.

12
00:04:57,033 --> 00:04:58,701
Now, are you the Speck Brothers?

13
00:04:58,868 --> 00:05:01,704
Did you purchase those men at the Greenville auction?

14
00:05:01,871 --> 00:05:04,499
- So what? - So I wish to parley with you.

15
00:05:04,665 --> 00:05:05,666
Speak English.

16
00:05:06,375 --> 00:05:07,960
I'm sorry.

17
00:05:08,127 --> 00:05:10,338
Please forgive me. It is a second language.

18
00:05:10,505 --> 00:05:13,883
Now, amongst your inventory, I've been led to believe...

19
00:05:14,050 --> 00:05:16,344
...is a specimen I'm keen to acquire.

20
00:05:16,511 --> 00:05:17,970
Hello, you poor devils.

21
00:05:19,305 --> 00:05:22,141
Is there one amongst you who was formerly a resident...

22
00:05:22,308 --> 00:05:25,311
...of the Carrucan plantation?

23
00:05:26,229 --> 00:05:28,356
I'm from the Carrucan plantation.

24
00:05:30,191 --> 00:05:31,566
Who said that?

25
00:05:31,567 --> 00:05:39,567
Subtitle www.movieddl.me

26
00:06:18,490 --> 00:06:20,284
What's your name?

27
00:06:24,288 --> 00:06:26,039
Django.

28
00:06:26,331 --> 00:06:28,876
Then you are exactly the one I'm looking for.

29
00:06:30,669 --> 00:06:33,046
Do you know who the Brittle Brothers are?

30
00:06:36,550 --> 00:06:37,593
Who are they?

31
00:06:40,095 --> 00:06:41,763
Big John.

32
00:06:42,431 --> 00:06:43,891
Ellis.

33
00:06:45,100 --> 00:06:46,393
Roger.

34
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:49,354
Sometime they call him Little Raj.

35
00:06:50,355 --> 00:06:52,733
They was overseers at the Carrucan plantation.

36
00:06:52,900 --> 00:06:53,984
Not anymore.

37
00:06:57,070 --> 00:07:01,367
Tell me, if you were to see any of these three gentlemen again...

38
00:07:01,534 --> 00:07:03,828
- ...would you recognise them? - Hey.

39
00:07:04,537 --> 00:07:07,040
- Stop talking to him like that. - Like what?

40
00:07:07,457 --> 00:07:08,499
Like that.

41
00:07:08,666 --> 00:07:11,169
My good man, I'm simply trying to ascertain...

42
00:07:11,336 --> 00:07:13,212
Speak English, goddamn it.

43
00:07:13,379 --> 00:07:15,381
Everybody calm down.

44
00:07:15,548 --> 00:07:19,218
I'm simply a customer trying to conduct a transaction.

45
00:07:19,385 --> 00:07:22,347
I don't care. No sale. Now, off with you.

46
00:07:22,931 --> 00:07:25,433
Don't be ridiculous. Of course they're for sale.

47
00:07:26,351 --> 00:07:27,769
Move it.

48
00:07:28,019 --> 00:07:32,732
My good man, did you simply get carried away with your dramatic gesture...

49
00:07:32,899 --> 00:07:36,736
...or are you pointing your weapon at me with lethal intention?

50
00:07:38,029 --> 00:07:39,739
Last chance, fancy pants.

51
00:07:40,990 --> 00:07:43,409
Oh, very well.

52
00:08:12,272 --> 00:08:16,610
I'm sorry to put a bullet in your beast. I didn't want you to do anything rash...

53
00:08:16,777 --> 00:08:19,363
...before you had a moment to come to your senses.

54
00:08:19,530 --> 00:08:22,908
You goddamn son of a bitch.

55
00:08:23,158 --> 00:08:24,535
You shot Roscoe!

56
00:08:24,702 --> 00:08:25,786
Well...

57
00:08:25,995 --> 00:08:27,413
And you killed Ace!

58
00:08:27,579 --> 00:08:30,624
I only shot your brother once he threatened to shoot me.

59
00:08:30,791 --> 00:08:32,251
And I do believe I have...

60
00:08:32,418 --> 00:08:33,669
One, two, three, four.

61
00:08:33,836 --> 00:08:36,755
- -Five witnesses who can attest to that fact.

62
00:08:36,922 --> 00:08:39,425
- Damn leg's busted. - No doubt.

63
00:08:39,591 --> 00:08:42,761
Now, if you could keep your caterwauling down to a minimum...

64
00:08:42,928 --> 00:08:46,432
...I'd like to finish my line of enquiry with young Django.

65
00:08:49,852 --> 00:08:51,729
God-fucking-damn it!

66
00:08:51,895 --> 00:08:53,397
As I was saying...

67
00:08:53,564 --> 00:08:57,776
...if you were to see the Brittle Brothers again, you could recognise them?

68
00:08:57,943 --> 00:08:59,319
Yeah.

69
00:08:59,862 --> 00:09:01,030
Sold American!

70
00:09:01,196 --> 00:09:02,322
So, Mr. Speck?

71
00:09:02,489 --> 00:09:05,200
Mr. Speck? How much for young Django here?

72
00:09:10,498 --> 00:09:13,251
That iron is nasty business.

73
00:09:18,381 --> 00:09:20,925
Oh, could you hold this for a moment?

74
00:09:22,552 --> 00:09:23,595
Thank you.

75
00:09:23,762 --> 00:09:26,306
Django? Get up on that horse.

76
00:09:26,473 --> 00:09:28,058
Also, if I were you...

77
00:09:28,224 --> 00:09:32,604
...I'd take that winter coat the dear departed Speck left behind.

78
00:09:46,284 --> 00:09:50,497
Nigger! Don't you touch my brother's coat.

79
00:10:01,674 --> 00:10:04,010
Goddamn it!

80
00:10:08,014 --> 00:10:10,725
One hundred, 10...

81
00:10:11,184 --> 00:10:12,727
...20...

82
00:10:13,103 --> 00:10:14,730
...and 5...

83
00:10:15,815 --> 00:10:17,274
...for young Django here.

84
00:10:17,441 --> 00:10:19,652
And since he won't be needing it anymore...

85
00:10:19,819 --> 00:10:22,154
...I'd like to purchase your brother's nag.

86
00:10:22,905 --> 00:10:25,032
Also, Mr. Speck...

87
00:10:25,199 --> 00:10:29,120
...I'm afraid I will require a bill of sale. Do you have one?

88
00:10:29,703 --> 00:10:32,790
You go to hell, dentist.

89
00:10:33,124 --> 00:10:34,917
I thought not.

90
00:10:35,084 --> 00:10:38,796
No worries. I come prepared.

91
00:10:42,842 --> 00:10:44,426
Thank you.

92
00:10:44,593 --> 00:10:48,389
This will serve nicely as a bill of sale.

93
00:11:05,781 --> 00:11:09,243
Now, as to you poor devils...

94
00:11:09,535 --> 00:11:11,370
So, as I see it...

95
00:11:11,537 --> 00:11:14,456
...when it comes to the subject of what to do next...

96
00:11:14,623 --> 00:11:17,459
...you gentlemen have two choices.

97
00:11:17,626 --> 00:11:18,752
One:

98
00:11:18,919 --> 00:11:22,716
Once I'm gone, you could lift that beast off the remaining Speck...

99
00:11:22,883 --> 00:11:24,885
...then carry him to the nearest town.

100
00:11:25,051 --> 00:11:28,638
Which would be at least 37 miles back the way you came.

101
00:11:28,805 --> 00:11:30,056
Or two:

102
00:11:30,849 --> 00:11:32,976
You could unshackle yourselves...

103
00:11:33,143 --> 00:11:34,436
...take that rifle...

104
00:11:34,603 --> 00:11:37,606
...put a bullet in his head, bury the two of them deep...

105
00:11:37,772 --> 00:11:41,484
...and then make your way to a more enlightened area of this country.

106
00:11:41,860 --> 00:11:43,069
Choice is yours.

107
00:11:43,236 --> 00:11:47,574
Oh, and on the off chance there are any astronomy aficionados amongst you...

108
00:11:47,741 --> 00:11:50,827
...the North Star is that one.

109
00:11:52,204 --> 00:11:53,788
Ta-ta.

110
00:12:10,222 --> 00:12:13,934
Now, wait a minute, fellas. Let's talk about this.

111
00:12:17,771 --> 00:12:21,691
You gotta be reasonable in a situation like this.

112
00:12:22,692 --> 00:12:25,821
I'm not a bad guy. I'm just doing my job.

113
00:12:25,988 --> 00:12:29,533
Blueberry, didn't I give you my last apple?

114
00:12:29,700 --> 00:12:30,952
Tell you what, boys:

115
00:12:31,118 --> 00:12:34,872
Take me to the doc in El Paso, I'll get you your freedom.

116
00:12:35,039 --> 00:12:36,207
No. No, please.

117
00:13:24,088 --> 00:13:25,464
All right, now.

118
00:13:25,673 --> 00:13:28,134
I'd like you to take two of these tonight...

119
00:13:28,302 --> 00:13:30,262
...and then in the morning...

120
00:13:32,222 --> 00:13:33,974
That's a nigger on a horse.

121
00:13:59,499 --> 00:14:01,335
What's everybody staring at?

122
00:14:01,501 --> 00:14:04,463
They ain't never seen no nigger on a horse before.

123
00:14:27,361 --> 00:14:29,571
Good morning, innkeeper.

124
00:14:30,822 --> 00:14:33,242
Two beers for two weary travellers.

125
00:14:33,409 --> 00:14:37,705
It's still a bit early. We won't be open for another hour.

126
00:14:37,872 --> 00:14:39,791
By then, we'll be serving breakfast.

127
00:14:43,086 --> 00:14:45,254
What the hell you think you're doing, boy?

128
00:14:45,421 --> 00:14:47,715
Get that nigger out of here.

129
00:14:52,470 --> 00:14:54,013
Help! Help!

130
00:14:54,180 --> 00:14:55,223
Innkeeper!

131
00:14:55,681 --> 00:14:58,601
Remember, get the sheriff, not the marshal.

132
00:14:58,768 --> 00:15:00,853
Sheriff! Help!

133
00:15:01,020 --> 00:15:02,730
Alas...

134
00:15:03,689 --> 00:15:06,776
...now we must act as our own bartender.

135
00:15:08,736 --> 00:15:10,613
Sit down, my boy.

136
00:15:20,289 --> 00:15:22,208
What kind of dentist are you?

137
00:15:24,210 --> 00:15:28,840
Despite that cart, I haven't practised dentistry in five years.

138
00:15:33,052 --> 00:15:36,097
But these days, I practise a new profession:

139
00:15:38,642 --> 00:15:39,893
Bounty hunter.

140
00:15:46,567 --> 00:15:48,819
Do you know what a bounty hunter is?

141
00:15:48,986 --> 00:15:50,154
No.

142
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:51,488
Well...

143
00:15:52,948 --> 00:15:57,077
...the way the slave trade deals in human lives for cash...

144
00:15:57,244 --> 00:15:59,913
...a bounty hunter deals in corpses.

145
00:16:00,998 --> 00:16:02,332
Hat.

146
00:16:15,637 --> 00:16:18,223
The state places a bounty on a man's head.

147
00:16:18,390 --> 00:16:21,059
I track that man, I find that man, I kill that man.

148
00:16:21,226 --> 00:16:25,272
After I've killed him, I transport that man's corpse back to the authorities.

149
00:16:25,439 --> 00:16:28,150
Sometimes that's easier said than done.

150
00:16:28,317 --> 00:16:32,946
I show that corpse to the authorities, proving indeed, I truly have killed him.

151
00:16:33,113 --> 00:16:35,866
At which point the authorities pay me the bounty.

152
00:16:36,033 --> 00:16:39,536
So, like slavery, it's a flesh-for-cash business.

153
00:16:41,121 --> 00:16:42,165
What's a bounty?

154
00:16:46,044 --> 00:16:47,545
It's like a reward.

155
00:16:48,046 --> 00:16:51,090
You kill people? And they give you a reward?

156
00:16:51,799 --> 00:16:53,134
Certain people, yeah.

157
00:16:53,468 --> 00:16:55,094
Bad people?

158
00:16:55,678 --> 00:16:58,264
Badder they are, bigger the reward.

159
00:16:58,723 --> 00:17:00,767
Which brings me to you.

160
00:17:01,100 --> 00:17:04,938
And I must admit, I'm at a bit of a quandary when it comes to you.

161
00:17:05,647 --> 00:17:07,941
On one hand, I despise slavery.

162
00:17:08,107 --> 00:17:11,319
On the other hand, I need your help.

163
00:17:11,486 --> 00:17:14,781
If you're not in a position to refuse, all the better.

164
00:17:15,573 --> 00:17:16,824
So for the time being...

165
00:17:16,991 --> 00:17:20,370
...I'm gonna make this slavery malarkey work to my benefit.

166
00:17:20,870 --> 00:17:23,581
Still, having said that...

167
00:17:24,332 --> 00:17:25,500
...I feel guilty.

168
00:17:27,210 --> 00:17:32,507
So I would like the two of us to enter into an agreement.

169
00:17:39,389 --> 00:17:41,349
I'm looking for the Brittle Brothers.

170
00:17:46,145 --> 00:17:49,441
However, at this endeavour, I'm at a slight disadvantage...

171
00:17:49,942 --> 00:17:52,820
...insofar as I don't know what they look like.

172
00:17:54,113 --> 00:17:56,865
But you do. Don't you?

173
00:17:57,032 --> 00:17:59,243
I know what they look like, all right.

174
00:17:59,410 --> 00:18:00,536
Good.

175
00:18:00,744 --> 00:18:02,871
So here's my agreement.

176
00:18:03,038 --> 00:18:05,124
You travel with me until we find them.

177
00:18:05,291 --> 00:18:06,500
Where we going?

178
00:18:06,667 --> 00:18:09,336
I hear at least two of them are overseeing in Gatlinburg...

179
00:18:09,503 --> 00:18:11,255
...but I don't know where.

180
00:18:11,630 --> 00:18:16,176
That means we visit every plantation in Gatlinburg till we find them.

181
00:18:16,343 --> 00:18:17,970
And when we find them...

182
00:18:18,470 --> 00:18:20,556
...you point them out and I kill them.

183
00:18:22,558 --> 00:18:24,018
You do that...

184
00:18:24,268 --> 00:18:28,564
...I agree to give you your freedom, $25 per Brittle Brother.

185
00:18:28,731 --> 00:18:30,107
That's $75.

186
00:18:30,274 --> 00:18:34,653
And, as if on cue, here comes the sheriff.

187
00:18:41,702 --> 00:18:45,164
Okay, boys. Fun's over.

188
00:18:46,206 --> 00:18:47,750
Come on out.

189
00:18:50,711 --> 00:18:54,841
All right, folks, calm down.

190
00:18:55,425 --> 00:18:57,594
Go about your business.

191
00:18:57,969 --> 00:19:00,513
These jokers will be gone soon.

192
00:19:02,474 --> 00:19:07,646
Now, why y'all wanna come into my town and start trouble?

193
00:19:07,812 --> 00:19:11,191
And scare all these nice people.

194
00:19:12,442 --> 00:19:15,195
You ain't got nothing better to do...

195
00:19:15,362 --> 00:19:18,490
...than to come into Bill Sharp's town...

196
00:19:18,657 --> 00:19:21,743
...and show your ass?

197
00:19:29,292 --> 00:19:31,795
What'd you just do to our sheriff?

198
00:19:44,599 --> 00:19:46,810
Now you can get the marshal.

199
00:19:48,269 --> 00:19:50,480
Marshal! Marshal!

200
00:19:50,647 --> 00:19:52,982
- Should we wait inside? - Can we just leave?

201
00:19:53,149 --> 00:19:54,484
After you.

202
00:19:56,946 --> 00:20:00,700
Move that buckboard a long ways across the street from the saloon.

203
00:20:01,075 --> 00:20:04,036
I want six men, six rifles behind it.

204
00:20:04,203 --> 00:20:06,455
I want two men, two rifles up on this roof.

205
00:20:06,622 --> 00:20:08,749
Two men, two rifles on that roof.

206
00:20:08,958 --> 00:20:11,794
All the barrels aimed at that front door.

207
00:20:12,294 --> 00:20:15,256
Somebody get poor Bill out of the goddamn street.

208
00:20:16,257 --> 00:20:18,175
You in the saloon.

209
00:20:18,843 --> 00:20:22,304
We got 100 rifles aimed at every way out of that building.

210
00:20:22,722 --> 00:20:26,058
You got one chance to get out of this alive.

211
00:20:26,767 --> 00:20:31,439
You and your nigger come out right now, and I mean right now.

212
00:20:32,481 --> 00:20:36,068
Is this the marshal I have the pleasure of addressing?

213
00:20:36,527 --> 00:20:37,987
Yes, it is.

214
00:20:38,154 --> 00:20:40,281
This is U.S. Marshal Gill Tatum.

215
00:20:40,448 --> 00:20:42,616
Na wunderbar, marshal.

216
00:20:43,159 --> 00:20:46,829
I have relieved myself of all weapons...

217
00:20:47,163 --> 00:20:49,957
...and just as you have instructed...

218
00:20:50,124 --> 00:20:52,793
...I am ready to step outside...

219
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:56,881
...with my hands raised above my head.

220
00:20:58,174 --> 00:21:00,426
I trust, as a representative...

221
00:21:00,594 --> 00:21:04,139
...of the criminal justice system of the United States of America...

222
00:21:04,306 --> 00:21:07,309
...I shan't be shot down in the street...

223
00:21:07,476 --> 00:21:10,145
...by either you or your deputies...

224
00:21:10,312 --> 00:21:13,064
...before I've had my day in court.

225
00:21:13,315 --> 00:21:15,317
You mean like you did our sheriff?

226
00:21:15,484 --> 00:21:17,527
Shot him down like a dog in the street.

227
00:21:17,694 --> 00:21:19,946
Yes, that's exactly what I mean.

228
00:21:20,113 --> 00:21:22,199
Do I have your word as a lawman...

229
00:21:22,365 --> 00:21:26,161
...not to shoot me down like a dog in the street?

230
00:21:29,122 --> 00:21:32,667
Well, much as we'd all enjoy seeing something like that...

231
00:21:32,834 --> 00:21:35,796
...ain't nobody gonna cheat the hangman in my town.

232
00:21:36,630 --> 00:21:39,633
Fair enough, marshal. Here we come.

233
00:21:41,510 --> 00:21:43,553
They're a little tense out there...

234
00:21:43,720 --> 00:21:47,432
...so don't make any quick movements and let me do the talking.

235
00:21:48,809 --> 00:21:50,268
Come ahead.

236
00:21:57,359 --> 00:22:00,320
- You unarmed? - Yes, indeed we are.

237
00:22:00,987 --> 00:22:04,282
Marshal Tatum, may I address you and your deputies...

238
00:22:04,449 --> 00:22:06,994
...and apparently the entire town of Daughtrey...

239
00:22:07,161 --> 00:22:09,789
...as to the incident that just occurred?

240
00:22:10,498 --> 00:22:11,749
Go on.

241
00:22:11,958 --> 00:22:13,125
Thank you.

242
00:22:13,292 --> 00:22:15,294
My name is Dr. King Schultz.

243
00:22:15,461 --> 00:22:18,840
Like yourself, marshal, I'm a servant of the court.

244
00:22:19,006 --> 00:22:20,800
The man lying dead in the dirt...

245
00:22:20,967 --> 00:22:24,762
...who the good people of Daughtrey saw fit to elect as their sheriff...

246
00:22:24,929 --> 00:22:27,056
...who went by the name of Bill Sharp...

247
00:22:27,223 --> 00:22:31,269
...is actually a wanted outlaw by the name of Willard Peck...

248
00:22:31,435 --> 00:22:34,021
...with a price on his head of $200.

249
00:22:34,188 --> 00:22:37,191
Now that's $200, dead or alive.

250
00:22:37,358 --> 00:22:38,651
The hell, you say.

251
00:22:38,818 --> 00:22:42,738
I'm aware this is probably disconcerting news.

252
00:22:42,905 --> 00:22:44,365
But I'm willing to wager...

253
00:22:44,532 --> 00:22:48,786
...this man was elected sheriff sometime in the past two years?

254
00:22:49,871 --> 00:22:52,957
- Yeah. - I know this because three years ago...

255
00:22:53,124 --> 00:22:56,586
...he was rustling cattle from the B.C. Corrigan Cattle Company...

256
00:22:56,752 --> 00:22:58,004
...of Lubbock, Texas.

257
00:22:58,170 --> 00:23:00,882
Now, this is a warrant...

258
00:23:01,048 --> 00:23:05,636
...made out by circuit court judge Henry Allen Laudermilk...

259
00:23:05,803 --> 00:23:07,763
...of Austin, Texas.

260
00:23:07,930 --> 00:23:09,682
You're encouraged to wire him.

