769
01:05:48,695 --> 01:05:51,114
Turn him around! Now, come...!

770
01:05:53,992 --> 01:05:55,744
Use your strength, boy!

771
01:05:56,328 --> 01:05:58,872
Come on, now! Use your strength!

772
01:06:00,457 --> 01:06:02,167
There you go.

773
01:06:03,793 --> 01:06:05,045
There you go!

774
01:06:05,212 --> 01:06:06,254
Look at that.

775
01:06:07,088 --> 01:06:10,175
See, I told you to put some more power in there.

776
01:06:10,342 --> 01:06:12,344
Do what I told you, boy.

777
01:06:12,511 --> 01:06:14,179
There you go.

778
01:06:14,347 --> 01:06:15,515
No.

779
01:06:15,681 --> 01:06:16,682
Do what I told you!

780
01:06:16,849 --> 01:06:20,394
Blind him black, boy! Blind him black!

781
01:06:22,021 --> 01:06:23,606
Oh, no, Luigi.

782
01:06:25,858 --> 01:06:26,901
Yeah!

783
01:06:44,418 --> 01:06:45,461
Finish him.

784
01:06:49,882 --> 01:06:51,467
Go on, boy, finish him.

785
01:06:56,097 --> 01:06:59,183
That's why they call him Big Fred. Worth every penny.

786
01:06:59,600 --> 01:07:01,435
Well, arrivederci, Luigi.

787
01:07:01,602 --> 01:07:03,854
Come on up, now, boy. Get yourself a rest.

788
01:07:04,021 --> 01:07:06,816
You did a fine job. A real fine job.

789
01:07:07,400 --> 01:07:08,985
Mercedes.

790
01:07:30,257 --> 01:07:31,717
Tequila.

791
01:07:41,476 --> 01:07:43,186
What's your name?

792
01:07:45,230 --> 01:07:46,815
Django.

793
01:07:49,109 --> 01:07:50,902
Can you spell it?

794
01:07:52,904 --> 01:07:56,908
D-J-A-N-G-O.

795
01:07:58,452 --> 01:07:59,995
The D is silent.

796
01:08:00,537 --> 01:08:02,122
I know.

797
01:08:09,755 --> 01:08:13,216
Mr. Moguy, I want you to take care of my new boy here.

798
01:08:13,383 --> 01:08:17,679
You find him a room with a soft bed, then bring him a pony to lick his pole.

799
01:08:17,846 --> 01:08:20,932
Be ready to travel to Candyland tomorrow morning, you hear?

800
01:08:21,099 --> 01:08:22,476
- Yes, sir. - Before you go...

801
01:08:22,643 --> 01:08:26,397
Roscoe, get Fred here a tall beer.

802
01:08:29,859 --> 01:08:32,945
You enjoy that, boy. You've earned it.

803
01:08:33,112 --> 01:08:34,489
Yes, sir.

804
01:08:43,498 --> 01:08:44,666
What's your name, boy?

805
01:08:45,249 --> 01:08:48,086
His name is Django Freeman.

806
01:08:51,089 --> 01:08:52,757
Where'd you dig him up?

807
01:08:52,924 --> 01:08:56,844
A fortuitous turn of events brought Django and myself together.

808
01:08:57,804 --> 01:09:00,098
I've heard tell about you.

809
01:09:00,556 --> 01:09:03,476
You been telling everybody them Mandingos ain't no good.

810
01:09:03,643 --> 01:09:07,397
Nothing nobody is selling is worth buying. I'm curious.

811
01:09:07,563 --> 01:09:10,066
What makes you such a Mandingo expert?

812
01:09:12,068 --> 01:09:14,487
I'm curious what makes you so curious.

813
01:09:17,824 --> 01:09:20,618
- What did you say, boy? - Calm down, Butch.

814
01:09:20,910 --> 01:09:22,203
No offence given...

815
01:09:22,912 --> 01:09:24,163
...none taken.

816
01:09:24,330 --> 01:09:25,915
Monsieur Candie...

817
01:09:26,082 --> 01:09:29,878
...I'd appreciate if you could direct your line of enquiry toward me.

818
01:09:30,045 --> 01:09:31,380
One...

819
01:09:32,005 --> 01:09:35,300
...you do not have a drink. Can I get you a refreshment?

820
01:09:35,467 --> 01:09:37,970
Yes. I'll have a beer.

821
01:09:38,137 --> 01:09:40,431
Roscoe, a beer for the man with the beard...

822
01:09:40,597 --> 01:09:44,435
...and I will have a Polynesian Pearl Diver. Do not spare the rum.

823
01:09:44,601 --> 01:09:46,061
Doc...

824
01:09:46,770 --> 01:09:50,107
...I am a seasoned slaver. You are... Well, you are a neophyte.

825
01:09:50,274 --> 01:09:53,360
I'm simply trying to ascertain if this cowboy here...

826
01:09:53,527 --> 01:09:55,487
...is taking advantage of you.

827
01:09:56,780 --> 01:10:00,367
With all due respect, Monsieur Candie...

828
01:10:00,534 --> 01:10:02,703
...I didn't seek you out for your advice.

829
01:10:02,870 --> 01:10:07,249
I sought you out to purchase a fighting nigger at above top-dollar market price.

830
01:10:07,416 --> 01:10:10,669
I was under the impression, when you granted me an audience...

831
01:10:10,836 --> 01:10:13,088
...it would be to discuss business.

832
01:10:15,716 --> 01:10:18,051
Well, we weren't talking business yet.

833
01:10:18,218 --> 01:10:20,888
We were discussing my curiosity.

834
01:10:22,806 --> 01:10:23,849
Thank you.

835
01:10:24,016 --> 01:10:26,894
Roscoe, Coco, go outside and play.

836
01:10:28,729 --> 01:10:31,982
Sheba, you stay right there.

837
01:10:32,232 --> 01:10:33,818
I know you didn't mean me.

838
01:10:37,155 --> 01:10:38,615
German.

839
01:10:39,073 --> 01:10:40,700
Now, according to Moguy...

840
01:10:40,950 --> 01:10:42,911
...if I do business with you...

841
01:10:43,077 --> 01:10:45,079
...I'm doing business with both y'all.

842
01:10:45,246 --> 01:10:47,707
He does the eyeballing, you the billfold?

843
01:10:47,874 --> 01:10:51,628
Well, you don't make it sound too flattering, but more or less, yeah.

844
01:10:54,130 --> 01:10:55,256
So...

845
01:10:55,757 --> 01:10:59,344
...Bright Boy, Moguy tells me you looked over my African flesh...

846
01:10:59,511 --> 01:11:01,763
...and you was none too impressed, huh?

847
01:11:01,930 --> 01:11:03,431
Not for top dollar.

848
01:11:05,433 --> 01:11:07,435
Then we got nothing more to talk about.

849
01:11:07,602 --> 01:11:09,771
You wanna buy a beat-ass nigger from me...

850
01:11:09,938 --> 01:11:12,398
...those are the beat-ass niggers I wanna sell.

851
01:11:12,565 --> 01:11:15,193
He don't wanna buy the niggers you wanna sell.

852
01:11:15,360 --> 01:11:18,571
He wants the nigger you don't wanna sell.

853
01:11:18,780 --> 01:11:23,368
Well, I don't sell the niggers I don't wanna sell.

854
01:11:25,328 --> 01:11:28,998
Well, you won't sell your best.

855
01:11:29,165 --> 01:11:31,543
You won't even sell your second best.

856
01:11:31,709 --> 01:11:35,213
But your third best? You don't want to sell him either.

857
01:11:35,380 --> 01:11:39,760
But if I made you an offer so ridiculous you'd be forced to consider it...

858
01:11:40,594 --> 01:11:42,263
...who knows what could happen?

859
01:11:44,723 --> 01:11:46,934
And what do you consider ridiculous?

860
01:11:47,810 --> 01:11:52,398
For a truly talented specimen, the right nigger?

861
01:11:53,858 --> 01:11:55,734
How much would you say, Django?

862
01:11:59,113 --> 01:12:01,323
Twelve thousand dollars.

863
01:12:05,619 --> 01:12:09,415
Well, gentlemen, you had my curiosity...

864
01:12:09,582 --> 01:12:11,876
...but now you have my attention.

865
01:12:25,306 --> 01:12:27,516
Willie. Willie.

866
01:12:27,683 --> 01:12:29,977
Hold up. Hold up.

867
01:12:30,978 --> 01:12:33,564
- Good morning, gentlemen. - Good Dr. Schultz.

868
01:12:33,939 --> 01:12:37,568
- Beautiful morning, isn't it? - You couldn't have picked a better one.

869
01:12:37,735 --> 01:12:40,696
Won't you take a ride with us here in the Victoria?

870
01:12:40,863 --> 01:12:42,157
Oh, thank you very much.

871
01:12:42,324 --> 01:12:44,784
You can tie your horse up back there.

872
01:12:52,751 --> 01:12:54,377
Django.

873
01:12:58,840 --> 01:13:02,594
Where I part company from many of my phrenologist colleagues...

874
01:13:02,761 --> 01:13:05,847
...is I believe there is a level above bright...

875
01:13:06,014 --> 01:13:08,808
...above talented, above loyal...

876
01:13:08,975 --> 01:13:12,187
...that a nigger can aspire to.

877
01:13:12,354 --> 01:13:16,858
Say, one nigger that just pops up in 10,000.

878
01:13:17,108 --> 01:13:18,652
The exceptional nigger.

879
01:13:19,653 --> 01:13:22,197
Bright day, huh, Bright Boy?

880
01:13:22,822 --> 01:13:24,032
The sun is up.

881
01:13:25,158 --> 01:13:27,077
It's shining on all of us.

882
01:13:31,790 --> 01:13:33,583
Have a seat, doc.

883
01:13:33,959 --> 01:13:36,211
Thank you. Quite an honour.

884
01:13:36,378 --> 01:13:38,171
- The honour is all ours. - Thank you.

885
01:13:38,588 --> 01:13:41,716
But I do believe that given time...

886
01:13:41,883 --> 01:13:45,095
...exceptional niggers like Bright Boy here...

887
01:13:45,512 --> 01:13:48,057
...become if not frequent...

888
01:13:48,683 --> 01:13:50,601
...more frequent.

889
01:13:52,103 --> 01:13:53,479
Right, boy?

890
01:13:54,355 --> 01:13:56,857
You are that 1 in 10,000.

891
01:13:57,024 --> 01:14:00,152
The name of the game is keep up, not catch up, nigger.

892
01:14:16,002 --> 01:14:18,796
- Touch your guns, you die. - Everybody calm down.

893
01:14:19,088 --> 01:14:21,215
Now, I saw the whole thing. No harm done.

894
01:14:21,382 --> 01:14:24,552
- Are you kidding me? This nigger just... - I said no harm done!

895
01:14:24,719 --> 01:14:26,721
Now take your hand off your pistol!

896
01:14:28,347 --> 01:14:31,559
Butch, that means you too.

897
01:14:32,351 --> 01:14:34,520
Everybody stop antagonizing my guest.

898
01:14:36,647 --> 01:14:39,025
Hoot, get back up on your horse.

899
01:14:39,692 --> 01:14:41,235
He broke my collarbone.

900
01:14:41,402 --> 01:14:43,946
For God's sake, somebody please help Hoot here...

901
01:14:44,113 --> 01:14:45,823
...back up on his goddamn horse.

902
01:14:45,990 --> 01:14:48,951
- Yes, sir, boss. - Oh, now, you are one lucky nigger.

903
01:14:49,785 --> 01:14:51,788
Better listen to your boss, white boy.

904
01:14:51,955 --> 01:14:54,416
I'm gonna go walking in the moonlight with you.

905
01:14:54,583 --> 01:14:56,376
You wanna hold my hand?

906
01:15:02,966 --> 01:15:05,761
Willie, take us home.

907
01:15:07,763 --> 01:15:09,765
Here we go. Start moving.

908
01:15:16,354 --> 01:15:17,814
Head them out.

909
01:16:03,027 --> 01:16:05,196
You got a problem with your eyeball, boy?

910
01:16:05,363 --> 01:16:07,615
- No, sir. - You want a boot heel in it?

911
01:16:08,908 --> 01:16:09,951
No, sir.

912
01:16:10,118 --> 01:16:12,870
Then you keep your goddamn eyeballs off me.

913
01:16:13,121 --> 01:16:16,624
Flash that look at me again, I'll give you a reason not to like me.

914
01:16:16,791 --> 01:16:18,334
Now move, nigger.

915
01:16:20,169 --> 01:16:22,380
You niggers are gonna understand something.

916
01:16:22,547 --> 01:16:24,757
I'm worse than any of these white men here.

917
01:16:24,924 --> 01:16:28,553
You get the molasses out your ass, keep your goddamn eyeballs off me.

918
01:16:28,719 --> 01:16:31,430
He is a rambunctious sort, ain't he?

919
01:16:31,597 --> 01:16:32,807
Indeed.

920
01:16:35,351 --> 01:16:38,813
May we stop for a moment so I may put a word in my man's ear?

921
01:16:38,980 --> 01:16:42,692
I'm expecting to fall in love once I see the specimens at Candyland...

922
01:16:42,859 --> 01:16:44,318
...so before that moment...

923
01:16:44,485 --> 01:16:48,197
...it would be good if I could have a confidential strategy meeting...

924
01:16:48,364 --> 01:16:50,491
...with my confidant.

925
01:16:53,494 --> 01:16:55,288
What the hell you doing?

926
01:16:55,454 --> 01:16:58,040
I confirmed that Broomhilda's at Candyland.

927
01:17:01,378 --> 01:17:04,131
- You're sure it's her? - He didn't call her by name...

928
01:17:04,298 --> 01:17:07,843
...but she's a young lady, whip marks on her back and speaks German.

929
01:17:08,010 --> 01:17:09,720
While it's not wise to assume...

930
01:17:09,887 --> 01:17:12,347
...in this instance, I think it's pretty safe.

931
01:17:12,514 --> 01:17:13,974
Point being...

932
01:17:14,141 --> 01:17:17,144
...don't get so carried away with your retribution.

933
01:17:17,311 --> 01:17:19,062
You lose sight of why we're here.

934
01:17:19,229 --> 01:17:23,692
- You think I lost sight of that? - Yes, I do. Stop antagonizing Candie.

935
01:17:23,859 --> 01:17:28,989
You're going to blow this whole charade, or more than likely get us both killed.

936
01:17:29,156 --> 01:17:33,869
And I, for one, don't intend to die in Chickasaw County, Mississippi, U.S.A.

937
01:17:34,036 --> 01:17:37,414
I'm not antagonizing him. I'm intriguing him.

938
01:17:37,581 --> 01:17:40,375
You're yelling abuse at these poor slaves.

939
01:17:40,542 --> 01:17:42,794
I recall the man...

940
01:17:43,003 --> 01:17:46,089
...who had me kill another man in front of his son...

941
01:17:46,256 --> 01:17:48,342
...and he didn't bat a eye.

942
01:17:49,551 --> 01:17:50,594
You remember that?

943
01:17:52,721 --> 01:17:54,181
Yeah, of course I remember.

944
01:17:54,348 --> 01:17:57,893
What you said was that this is my world...

945
01:17:58,644 --> 01:18:01,063
...and in my world you gotta get dirty.

946
01:18:01,813 --> 01:18:05,026
So that's what I'm doing, I'm getting dirty.

947
01:18:08,446 --> 01:18:11,950
Well, you're paraphrasing a tad...

948
01:18:13,076 --> 01:18:15,161
...but that was the general gist.

949
01:18:18,957 --> 01:18:20,875
See you at Candyland.

950
01:18:28,091 --> 01:18:31,052
All right, niggers, back at it.

951
01:18:31,928 --> 01:18:34,180
That means you too, Moonlight.

952
01:19:21,145 --> 01:19:22,187
I'll be.

953
01:19:22,563 --> 01:19:24,189
D'Artagnan!

954
01:19:24,440 --> 01:19:27,568
Now, boy, why do a fool thing like run off?

955
01:19:27,735 --> 01:19:30,112
I can't fight no more, Monsieur Candie.

956
01:19:30,279 --> 01:19:31,405
Yes, you can.

957
01:19:31,572 --> 01:19:34,825
You might not be able to win, but your ass can fight.

958
01:19:35,284 --> 01:19:39,163
Mr. Stonesipher, would you shut these dogs up? I cannot hear myself think.

959
01:19:39,330 --> 01:19:41,915
Quieten down, Marsha! Marsha, hush up!

960
01:19:42,082 --> 01:19:43,542
Marsha! Hush up!

961
01:19:44,084 --> 01:19:47,629
Hey! Get these goddamn dogs away from this nigger!

962
01:19:56,680 --> 01:20:01,101
- Well, now, boy, get on out that tree. - Yes, sir.

963
01:20:24,501 --> 01:20:26,461
How long was he loose?

964
01:20:26,753 --> 01:20:29,923
A night. Day.

965
01:20:30,173 --> 01:20:32,092
Half the other night.

966
01:20:32,801 --> 01:20:34,636
How far he get off the property?

967
01:20:34,803 --> 01:20:39,682
About 20 miles off prop. Pretty far considering that limp he got.

968
01:20:41,434 --> 01:20:44,771
Mr. Moguy, who was D'Artagnan supposed to fight on Friday?

969
01:20:44,938 --> 01:20:46,898
One of this new lot.

970
01:20:47,649 --> 01:20:50,777
Way he looks now, a blind Indian wouldn't bet a bead on him.

971
01:20:50,944 --> 01:20:53,780
Please, Monsieur Candie, I ain't got it in me no more.

972
01:20:53,947 --> 01:20:57,325
Now, now, now. Now, no begging.

973
01:20:57,534 --> 01:21:00,328
No playing on my soft heart.

974
01:21:03,540 --> 01:21:06,626
- You in trouble now, son. - Yes, sir.

975
01:21:08,878 --> 01:21:12,674
You know, I done paid $500 for you.

976
01:21:12,841 --> 01:21:15,051
When I pay $500...

977
01:21:15,218 --> 01:21:19,473
...I expect to get five fights out of a nigger before he roll over and play dead.

978
01:21:19,640 --> 01:21:20,683
Sir.

979
01:21:20,850 --> 01:21:23,894
Gotta understand I'm running a business here.

980
01:21:24,270 --> 01:21:27,064
- You fought three fights. - But I won every one.

981
01:21:27,231 --> 01:21:28,691
Yes, you did. Yes, you did.

982
01:21:28,858 --> 01:21:32,570
But that last one, you muddled the line between winning and losing.

983
01:21:35,656 --> 01:21:37,783
Still, the fact remains:

984
01:21:37,992 --> 01:21:41,662
I pay $500, I want five goddamn fights.

985
01:21:41,996 --> 01:21:44,248
So, what about my $500, huh?

986
01:21:46,208 --> 01:21:48,544
What about my $500?

987
01:21:49,545 --> 01:21:51,130
You gonna reimburse me?

988
01:21:57,303 --> 01:21:59,638
You even know what "reimburse" means?

989
01:22:08,022 --> 01:22:09,773
I'll reimburse you.

990
01:22:13,569 --> 01:22:14,695
You will?

991
01:22:15,988 --> 01:22:17,448
Yep.

992
01:22:20,201 --> 01:22:22,495
You'll pay $500...

993
01:22:23,120 --> 01:22:26,666
...for practically a one-eyed old Joe ain't fit to push a broom?

994
01:22:26,833 --> 01:22:27,876
No, he won't.

995
01:22:30,003 --> 01:22:32,422
He just tired of you toying with him is all.

996
01:22:33,173 --> 01:22:35,133
Matter of fact, so am I.

997
01:22:35,425 --> 01:22:37,719
We ain't paying a penny for that pickaninny.

998
01:22:37,886 --> 01:22:40,639
Ain't got no use for him. Ain't that right, doc?

999
01:22:41,556 --> 01:22:42,849
You heard him.

1000
01:22:51,942 --> 01:22:56,530
You're gonna have to excuse Mr. Stonesipher's slack-jawed gaze.

1001
01:22:56,696 --> 01:22:59,991
He ain't never seen a nigger like you ever in his life.

1002
01:23:00,158 --> 01:23:02,160
Ain't that right, Mr. Stonesipher?

1003
01:23:04,538 --> 01:23:06,081
That's right.

1004
01:23:06,873 --> 01:23:08,333
For that matter...

1005
01:23:09,668 --> 01:23:11,211
...nor have I.

1006
01:23:17,259 --> 01:23:18,718
Now...

1007
01:23:19,427 --> 01:23:23,265
...seeing as you won't pay a penny for this pickaninny here...

1008
01:23:25,183 --> 01:23:28,437
...you won't mind me handling this nigger any way I see fit?

1009
01:23:29,605 --> 01:23:31,482
He's your nigger.

1010
01:23:34,902 --> 01:23:35,945
Mr. Stonesipher?

1011
01:23:37,947 --> 01:23:41,576
Let Marsha and her bitches send D'Artagnan to nigger heaven.

1012
01:23:41,826 --> 01:23:43,661
Marsha!

1013
01:23:43,828 --> 01:23:45,788
Marsha, hey, get him!

1014
01:23:48,499 --> 01:23:50,251
Get him, get him!

1015
01:24:23,951 --> 01:24:28,539
Your boss looks green around the gills for a blood sport like nigger fighting.

1016
01:24:28,706 --> 01:24:33,086
No. He just ain't used to seeing a man ripped apart by dogs is all.

1017
01:24:36,006 --> 01:24:37,466
You are used to it?

1018
01:24:37,633 --> 01:24:41,136
I'm just a little more used to Americans than he is.

1019
01:24:41,845 --> 01:24:45,140
Now, Monsieur Candie...

1020
01:24:45,307 --> 01:24:47,017
...whenever you're ready.

1021
01:24:47,351 --> 01:24:51,563
